Curtain call, part six : Broadway!Tom x fem! reader

masterlist

part one | part two | part three | part four | part five | part six | part seven

summary: y/n, a young actress, finally able to make her big break in the broadway world as Zoe in Dear Evan Hansen. The whole cast and crew is extremely welcoming and kind, all expect for the charming tom holland, a boy who just can’t help but give her a hard time, who just happens to be playing the main character and love interest

word count : 1178

warnings : unedited haha

song mentioned : falling slowly - once

previously on curtain call : “Extremely tiring, but very fun.” He answered as he led her to middle of his rehearsal room which he’d set a red and white checkered blanket on the ground. An ikea bag filled with boxes was resting on top of the blanket, which was surrounded by fake candles.

-

“Woah.” Was her reaction at the simple yet romantic sight.

“Woah as in good or woah as in bad?” The blond boy asked nervously, removing his hand from her back.

“Woah as in amazing!” She turned her head, facing him with a grin. “It’s beautiful Harrison!”

The girl quickly made her way to the blanket and sat down, letting herself find a comfortable position before eagerly waiting for her date to join her.

Letting out a small giggle, he jogged to where she sitting and joined her on the ground. He reached out for the bag with foot and pulled out two sandwiches.

“I didn’t know what you liked so I kinda just got you the sundance sandwich at my local sandwich store. If you don’t like it, I could give you my simple ham and cheese one.” He nervously rambled as he handed her the mentioned food.

“Don’t worry about it, it looks wonderful.” Her left hand grabbed the sandwich while her opposite one settled on his thigh as a way to reassure him, making the blue eyed boy blush.

“Okay great.” He grinned as their eyes met.

“Now Harrison, tell me about yourself.” She said, moving the hand that was on his thigh to behind her back so she’d be able to lean on it as she took a bite out of her food.

“If you insist darling.” He teased, taking into account that the pet name mad ether blush before continuing. “Well, from what you can deduct from my accent is that I was born in England. I went to the BRIT School, which is like this huge acting school in london. I moved to New York about a year ago. I’ve had my eyes set on broadway since I was young so naturally when I saw that newsies was being revived and was holding auditions, I jumped to the occasion. So yeah, that’s about it.”

“Im honestly so glad they revived newsies because it’s been like one of my favorite musicals ever.” She turned to him with a small smile after he finished his story.

“I’d heard about it before but, to tell the truth, i didn’t know much about it.”

“No way! Shut up!” She gasped as a laugh escaped her lips.

“I didn’t say anything.” He smirked, hoping she’d catch his subtle reference to the classic movie mean girls which only made her double in laughter.

“Don’t choke on your food love.” He managed to say before joining in her laughter.

When their laughter died down, the girl just stared into his eyes with a huge smile on her lips which the boy mirrored.

“Hold up just a minute.” Harrison said grabbing his phone and scrolling for something that his date would enjoy.

The opening notes to a song that sounded very familiar to y/n, started playing on a small speaker close to her. The boy started getting up and extended his hand for his date. She eagerly put her food down and grabbed his hand, standing up herself.

“I dont know you, but I want you.”

As the lyrics to the song started to be sung, Harisson hesitantly placed his hands around her waist, his hands relaxing when the girl’s arms found their way around his neck.

As the song Falling slowly from the musical Once continued, the pair slow danced around the room lot by small led candles. They each gazed into each other’s eyes, the girl getting lost in his piercing blue eyes while the boy took the time to memorize every beautiful aspect of her face, from her e/c eyes to her pale pink lips.

Her head rested on his chest, meaning she was able to hear his heart racing, making her giggle slightly, resulting in him blushing.

Harrison placed his head on top of hers while she slowly started humming to the song as it came close to his its end, meaning the most magical thing in his life was coming to a close.

As the closing notes started playing, she looked up at him, his eyes mirroring hers but discreetly and nervously sending glances to her lips. Giggling, she nodded and he leaned in, placing his slightly rough lips against her soft plump ones. Everything about that moment was magical, and Harrison wished he could just stop time so that he’d stay in this moment forever, but alas, that’s not how life works.

The romantic tension in the air disappeared as soon as a phone started obnoxiously ringing. Breaking the kiss, y/n started blushing madly as she realized it her phone.

“Shit, i’m sorry.” The girl nervously apologized as she quickly grabbed her phone to answer the call, leaving the boy standing there confused.

“Hey y/n.” The voice on the other line said nervously, which she recognized as her roommate.

“Hey Anya, what’s up?” She asked, using her free hand to fiddle with the end of her dress.

“It’s about my Dimitri.” A small sob escaped her lips, and y/n quickly made the connection.

“I’ll be right over.” She reassured and hung up, turning to her date nervously.

“I’m sorry I have to cut this short Harrison, tonight was absolutely amazing but somethings happening to a close friend of mine and she needs my support now.” The girl apologized, grabbing her back and sending him an apologetic look.

“Yeah, yeah, it’s cool. I hope everything’s gonna be alright for you friend.” He waved his hand, dismissing it.

“Thanks for being this understanding, I’ll try to make it up to you soon enough.” She quickly pecked his lips being rushing out of the room to get to her apartment.

Harrison sighed as he packed up everything, dissapointed that the best time in his life was cut short, but hopefully they’d go on a second date.

When he arrived home, he jumped on his bed and just stared at the wall.

“How’d the date go Haz?” His best friend and roommate asked, leaning against the doorframe.

“She had to leave early, something about her friend.” Harrison looked up at Tom who sent him a sympathetic look.

“There’s a new tub of rocky road ice cream in the freezer if you want it.” Tom informed him, before turning around, leaving his roommate to wallow in the ending of his date.

Little did Harrison know was that Tom was hoping the date would flop, he had started falling for the girl he took on a date that night since the first day they had met. Y/N instantly caught his attention, she had the most beautiful voice and personality that Tom had ever heard and met.

He never wanted to feel this way, since his closest friend felt the same about his costar, but in the end, he was the first to make a move, which meant that Tom would have to do something soon if he wanted to show the girl he was interested.

But in the end, it was whoever y/n fell for that be able to have her as their girlfriend.

taglist (open) : @starkravingparker, @spiderling-tom, @sheismental, @demigodnamedathena, @cailster

if you’d like to be tagged, just drop an ask!

He never wanted to feel this way, since his closest friend felt the same about his costar, but in the end, he was the first to make a move, which meant that Tom would have to do something soon if he wanted to show the girl he was interested.

But in the end, it was whoever y/n fell for that be able to have her as their girlfriend.
